<TITLE> RAB, police men held on extortion charge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, Feb 26 (bdnews24.com)  Rangpur police on Thursday arrested two members of RAB and police on charge of extortion of Tk 1 lakh. The arrested are RAB-5 constable Abul Hossain and Rangpur police special branch assistant sub-inspector (ASI) Mohammad Nasir. Another RAB sub-inspector (SI) Golam Rasul, also allegedly involved in the extortion, escaped arrest and has gone into hiding. The trio was allegedly involved in extortion of Tk 1 lakh from Atiar Rahman, an Indian businessman. Nasiruddin, a relative of Atiar, filed a case with Rangpur Kotwali police station. Investigating officer of the case, Noor Alam told bdnews24.com: "A person named Rakib was arrested in the case on Friday. During grilling, he revealed the involvement of the two RAB members and the police officer." "ASI Nasir was arrested on Thursday morning and RAB handed over constable Abul Hossain in the night after being informed of the incident. However SI Golam Rasul managed to escape," said Noor Alam. bdne
